article.description: — Antonio Daye, Jr. had 23 points as Florida International defeated Florida Gulf Coast 85-69 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Daye, Jr. leads FIU over Florida Gulf Coast 85-69
article.linkText: Daye, Jr. leads FIU over Florida Gulf Coast 85-69
article.story: FORT MYERS, Fla. -- — Antonio Daye, Jr. had 23 points as Florida International defeated Florida Gulf Coast 85-69 on Wednesday night. Daye, Jr. hit 8 of 10 shots. He added six assists. Radshad Davis had 16 points and eight rebounds for FIU (5-1). Eric Lovett added 14 points. Dimon Carrigan had seven rebounds and four blocks. Caleb Catto had 22 points for the Eagles (3-2). Cyrus Largie added 12 points and nine rebounds. Dakota Rivers had 10 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
